    "candidate.decision_history": {
      "risk": "critical",
      "ground_truth_scope": "Agent recommendations are admitted and keyed by logical organization/role/candidate identity even when their physical evidence application is replaced or soft-deleted; an active related-role membership remains actionable while a deleted ordinary application remains blocked. Recruiter-facing queues and tools expose only live logical subjects, and every active card remains bound to its exact current membership application rather than following a replacement source. Immutable audit rows remain available after a subject is erased or removed, but candidate-derived reasoning, evidence, notes, and other PII are redacted. A recruiter's explicit discard remains suppressed until the acting logical role's own score, CV, assessment, threshold, or policy inputs materially change; physical owner/application drift cannot override that human decision, including for direct and rolling-compatible related roles. Recommendations are filtered independently by created and resolved time, ordered deterministically, and never presented as proof that a workflow action completed. Policy feedback and nightly labels resolve the same role/candidate subject.",
      "required_surfaces": [
        "rest",
        "public_mcp",
        "taali_chat",
        "agent_chat",
        "autonomous_agent",
        "frontend"
